<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANTHONY (TONY) MONTALBANO; SINGER, SALON OPERATOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anthony (Tony) Montalbano, 67, who as Tony Montell sang in such Broadway 
musicals as "Mexican Hayride," "Around the World in 80 Days," "High Button 
Shoes," "Kiss Me Kate" and "Polonaise." After leaving New York in 1959, he came 
to Los Angeles and took over the beauty salon in the downtown Hilton, which he 
operated for many years before joining the wardrobe department at Santa Anita 
and Hollywood Park. In North Hollywood on Tuesday of cardiac arrest after 
surgery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
