<HEADLINE>
<P>
VIOLENCE IN EL SALVADOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In his plausible account of the woes of Central America, Schram alludes to the 
Soviet-Cuban funneling of military aid to Nicaragua and the rebels is El 
Salvador. Immediately above it is a Conrad cartoon about El Salvador in the 
form of a crucifix fashioned from a gun labeled "Made in U.S.A." 
</P>
<P>
Conrad needs to be told that the old liberal wheeze about everything wrong in 
the world being America's fault is now as passe as the Berlin Wall. 
</P>
<P>
TONY THOMAS 
</P>
<P>
Burbank 
</P>
