IMAGE AWAY THE PAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: I would appreciate an explanation of what is meant by "imaging" when 
it applies to efforts to reduce stress. 
</P>
<P>
Answer: Imaging refers to the practice of thinking about something pleasant or 
about a positive experience. This may help reduce stress brought about by a 
painful experience. 
</P>
<P>
For Malcolm, Syracuse, N.Y.: An estimated 25%-35% of migraine patients are 
estimated to be visually impaired to some extent. The impairment is related to 
the patient's age and the period of time he has been experiencing the attacks. 
Why the visual impairment occurs is not known. 
</P>
