<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP LP CHART; 
</P>
<P>
'STORM FRONT' MOVING UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nobody expected Billy Joel's "Storm Front" to take the Billboard pop album 
chart by storm -- but it has. His album inched up a notch to No. 2 and should 
take over the top spot in the next week or two. Joel just might have matching 
No. 1's -- the top pop album and single. Right now he has matching No. 2's. His 
single, "We Didn't Start the Fire" is also No. 2 on the pop singles chart. 
Whitesnake's "Slip of the Tongue" is the hottest new album on the chart, 
jetting to No. 13 in just two weeks. Shades of the '60s -- two guitar heroes 
have albums in the Top 30: Joe Satriani's high-flying "Flying in a Blue Dream" 
(No. 23) and Eric Clapton's "Journeyman" (No. 30). 
</P>
<P>
* Phil Collins' "But Seriously" debuted at a relatively low No. 82 but look for 
it to take a flying leap into the Top 20 next week. His single, "Another Day in 
Paradise," is No. 6 on the pop chart and just might reach No. 1 in the next few 
weeks. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
