<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sandra Bartley of Van Nuys will compete in the Sports Car Club of America's 
annual Fall Classic Enduro on Saturday at Willow Springs International Raceway 
near Rosamond. 
</P>
<P>
Bartley, a veteran Indy Pace Car Team driver and celebrity spokesperson for the 
California Assn. of Highway Safety Leaders, will team with Doug Dwyre of Palos 
Verdes on the nine-turn, 2.5-mile road course. 
</P>
<P>
The three-hour race will have a field of 70 cars from the Improved Touring and 
Showroom Stock classes. This is the final weekend of the Cal Club Region of the 
SCCA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
