on the East Coast. The weather caused some headaches for holiday travelers, and 
the oversized balloon floats in the annual Macy's parade got a frosting as New 
York City saw its first Thanksgiving snowfall in 51 years. The storm also 
dropped several inches of snow in Washington, D.C., left, where Capitol Hill 
was transformed into a sledder's delight. AL STEPHENSON / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
