<P>
RETIREE WINS $4.6 MILLION PLAYING SLOTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 76-year-old Las Vegas retiree won $4.6 million on a dollar slot machine at 
the new Mirage resort just hours after its grand opening, a casino spokesman 
said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Elmer Sherwin won $4,653,697.80 on a Megabucks dollar slot machine at the 
lavish new hotel-casino about 9:15 p.m. Wednesday. The Mirage, the newest 
resort on the Strip, opened shortly after noon. 
</P>
<P>
Sherwin had been playing the machine for about 90 minutes and fed it about $100 
before hitting the jackpot, the spokesman said. Sherwin worked for General 
Electric in Cleveland before retiring and moving to Las Vegas about five years 
ago, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The check presentation is scheduled today at the hotel after state gaming 
officials verify the jackpot, which will be paid in annual installments over a 
20-year period. 
</P>
<P>
A Mirage spokesman claimed that the jackpot was the largest ever won at a slot 
machine in Las Vegas. A jackpot of about $6 million was won in Reno a few years 
ago, the Mirage spokesman said. 
