<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN DIES IN CRASH NORTH OF NEWHALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Green Valley man was the first traffic fatality of the Thanksgiving weekend 
in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Kenneth Klemm, 57, lost control of his Datsun on Bouquet Canyon Road north of 
Newhall shortly after midnight Thursday and plowed into a rocky hillside, said 
Officer Monty Keifer of the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
Klemm died at Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital about 2 p.m., Keifer said. 
</P>
<P>
Klemm was not wearing a seat belt at the time of the accident and appeared to 
have been drinking, according to the CHP report. 
</P>
<P>
The day before the accident was Klemm's birthday, officers said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
