<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARMED WOMAN SHOT BY S.D. POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An armed unidentified woman was shot twice in the leg by a San Diego police 
officer Thursday, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Police responded to a 6:50 p.m. call at 3372 31st St. of a man and woman 
fighting. When the officers arrived, they were confronted by a woman armed with 
a shotgun. An officer fired twice, striking her in the leg. She was taken to 
Mercy hospital for treatment, where she was listed in critical but stable 
condition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
