Sinatra to Cross the Line: Frank Sinatra said he will perform scheduled 
engagements at Bally's in Las Vegas Dec. 4-9 and Dec. 26-31 despite an ongoing 
strike by musicians. "The holiday season is here and it's time for everyone to 
get back to work," the singer said in a prepared statement. Sinatra refused to 
cross picket lines in Las Vegas for previous shows. The singer's decision was 
seen as a major blow to Musicians Local 369, which has been on strike against 
Bally's and four other resorts since summer. SHAUNA SNOW 
