<P>
Loring Gives Thanks: Actress and singer Gloria Loring hosts the third annual 
"Thanks for Giving" Juvenile Diabetes Foundation special Sunday on USA Cable 
Network. "I'm trying to save my son's life," Loring says of her work with the 
telethon-like program. Her 15-year-old son Brennan has the disease. Loring said 
the special, which airs from 4-8 p.m., raised almost $4 million for diabetes 
research last year, and that she hopes even more will be raised Sunday. The 
all-star lineup scheduled to appear with Loring includes Alabama, the Jets, 
Poison and the Oak Ridge Boys; as well as Mary Tyler Moore, Ed Asner, Fred 
Savage, Susan Ruttan, Belinda Carlisle, Richard Mulligan, Alan Thicke, Cheech 
Marin and Edward James Olmos. SHAUNA SNOW 
