<TEXT>
<P>
A Birmingham, Ala., judge who issued an arrest warrant for Siran Stacy said the 
Alabama tailback will be given extra time to pay off his fine for speeding and 
driving with a suspended license. 
</P>
<P>
North Courtland traffic court Judge Rod Alexander said he talked with Stacy 
Wednesday, a day after issuing the warrant for his arrest when he didn't 
complete payment on a $192 fine. He said Stacy misunderstood the instructions 
on the ticket. 
</P>
<P>
Stacy was ticketed earlier this fall for speeding and driving with a suspended 
license. He pleaded guilty to the charges at an Oct. 17 hearing and made 
partial payment on the fine, with instructions to pay the balance by Tuesday's 
court date. 
</P>
<P>
When payment was not received and Stacy did not appear in court, Alexander 
routinely issued the arrest warrant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
