<TEXT>
<P>
Seattle Seahawks safety Paul Moyer reportedly has a ruptured disk in his neck 
that will sideline him the rest of the season and could end his football 
career. 
</P>
<P>
Moyer suffered a reoccurrence of a "stinger" -- a burning sensation usually 
around the neck area -- in Sunday's loss to the New York Giants, said Dave 
Neubert, team spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
Moyer has had the problem several times since he suffered a concussion in the 
Seahawks' Nov. 12 game against Cleveland and was sent to a specialist, Neubert 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Reports say the examination revealed the ruptured disc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
