<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN SMITH and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHRISTMAS TREE WARS: Fashion Island once boasted that the eight-story white 
firs erected there each Christmastime were the tallest in the nation, but the 
Douglas fir at the National Enquirer's offices in Florida proved to be one 
story taller. . . . After winning that commercial tree derby in 1987, the 
Enquirer retired from competition, but Florida seems intent on regaining the 
title. . . . This year's 110-footer at Fashion Island will come up short when 
Miami unveils it 144-foot tree. . . . The all-time record: a 221-foot Douglas 
fir at a Seattle shopping center in 1950. Steve Emmons 
</P>
