<P>
BONANZA: The holidays mark the beginning of the annual California gold rush for 
store owners -- and in Orange County in particular. . . . The average 
general-merchandise store here grossed $3.9 million last December, much higher 
than the $3-million national average. . . . Yet, the mother lode is even richer 
elsewhere. The average was higher in Los Angeles, Oakland, San Jose, Newark, 
N.J., and Bridgeport, Conn. . . . The highest average was in New York City, a 
whopping $8.4 million. Steve Emmons 
