<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
5 SHOT, 2 KILLED, IN WESTLAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men were shot and killed and three others were wounded, including a 
16-year-old pregnant girl shot in the stomach, all within the same Westlake 
neighborhood on the first night of the Thanksgiving holiday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Three of the shootings were linked to an ongoing territorial war between an 
established Latino gang and a newly formed, but unusually reckless, gang made 
up mostly of first-generation Salvadoran youths, said Los Angeles Police 
Detective Andy Cicoria. 
</P>
<P>
The shootings began at 4:45 p.m. Thursday when a 26-year-old woman "walking on 
the sidewalk and minding her own business caught a stray bullet in the neck," 
said Detective Terry Wessel. The woman was paralyzed from the neck down but was 
listed in stable condition Friday at County-USC Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
At 9:30 p.m. the 16-year-old girl was shot in the stomach and left knee in a 
drive-by incident, Wessel said. The girl was hospitalized in critical 
condition, but the condition of her 4-month-old fetus was not immediately 
known. 
</P>
<P>
Another man died a block and a half away in a gang-related shooting about 6 
a.m. today, Wessel said. 
</P>
<P>
In an incident apparently unrelated to the gang war, another man was shot to 
death late Thursday in a drug-related incident at the intersection of 6th 
Street and Westlake Boulevard, Wessel said. 
</P>
<P>
"They were dropping like flies around here," Wessel said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
