THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
PHOENIX'S COACH TO SWITCH QBS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHOENIX 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Phoenix Cardinals interim head Coach Hank Kuhlmann has decided to change 
quarterbacks and will give second-year pro Tom Tupa his second career NFL start 
in Sunday's game here against Tampa Bay. 
</P>
<P>
Kuhlmann, a fourth-year assistant who took over Monday for the fired Gene 
Stallings, said he asked offensive coordinator Jim Shofner for a recommendation 
Wednesday and Shofner suggested Tupa. 
</P>
<P>
The 6-foot-4 Tupa, a third-round draft pick in 1988 out of Ohio State, made his 
first career start here Oct. 15 against the Eagles and completed 14 of 41 
passes for 266 yards. But he also threw six interceptions and was sacked six 
times in a 17-5 loss. 
</P>
<P>
In last week's 37-14 road loss to the Rams, Stallings benched Gary Hogeboom 
early and Tupa completed 7 of 12 passes for 114 yards and one TD before rookie 
Tim Rosenbach finished up in his NFL debut. 
</P>
</TEXT>
